Actors represent external entities that interact with CookSnap â€“ Smart Recipe Recommendation System Using Grocery Images.
Identifying actors helps in understanding system interactions and defining appropriate use cases.

The following actors have been identified:

User (Home Cook / Student / Working Professional)
Initiates grocery image upload, views detected ingredients, receives recipe recommendations, and filters recipes based on preferences.

Admin (System Administrator)
Manages recipe data, monitors system usage, manages user access, and generates basic system reports.

Image Recognition System (AI Module)
Processes uploaded grocery images and detects ingredients using image recognition techniques.

Notification System
Sends alerts or messages to users regarding successful image upload, recipe availability, or system responses.

These actors interact with the CookSnap system to ensure efficient ingredient detection, accurate recipe recommendation, and smooth overall system operation.
